<title>USA: Wang Labs CEO gets $8 mln bonus to stay - WSJ.</title>
<headline>Wang Labs CEO gets $8 mln bonus to stay - WSJ.</headline>
<dateline>NEW YORK 1997-03-31</dateline>
<text>
<p>Wang Laboratories Inc gave its chairman and chief executive officer Joseph Tucci an $8 million cash and stock bonus after he turned down an offer to join Novell Inc, the Wall Street Journal said in Monday's electronic edition.</p>
<p>Tucci encouraged the company to rewrite his contract and give him a $4 million retention bonus, the paper said, citing Wang officials. They also promised to give him 230,000 shares of restricted stock, the paper said.</p>
<p>((New York newsdesk 212-859-1610))</p>
